
[1]laconical

   LACON'ICAL, a. [l. laconicus, from Laconia or Lacomes, the Spartans.]

   1. Short; brief; pithy; sententious; expressing much in few words,
   after the manner of the Spartans; as a laconic phrase.

   2. Pertaining to Sparta or Lacedemonia.
